http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/title.value: National Standards for High School Psychology Curricula

http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: The goal of the National Standards for High School Psychology Curricula is to help teachers and others responsible for the development of psychology curriculum at the secondary school level develop an accurate, comprehensive, and developmentally appropriate introductory psychology course aimed at students in grades 9 through 12.
